node.title: Victoria has recorded 1,061 new local COVID cases and four deaths
node.alt: Two health workers in protective gear.
node.description: There are now 11,331 active cases of the virus in Victoria, as tighter border rules come into force to respond to the new Omicron variant.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,061\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and four\u00a0deaths as tighter border rules have come into force to respond\u00a0to the new Omicron variant.\u00a0", "There are now 11,331\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 503\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.", "As part of precautionary measures to deal with the Omicron variant,\u00a0all overseas arrivals in Victoria are now required to isolate at home for 72 hours.", "Additionally, anyone who has visited one of the nine southern African countries of concern\u00a0\u2014\u00a0 Botswana, Zimbabwe, Malawi, South Africa, Namibia, Eswatini, Lesotho, Mozambique and the Seychelles\u00a0\u2014\u00a0in the past 14 days must undergo hotel quarantine for a fortnight.", "", "
Professor Bruce Thompson is\u00a0urging unvaccinated people to get the\u00a0COVID-19 jab, amid growing concerns about the Omicron variant. \u00a0(ABC News)
", "Professor Bruce Thompson, lead epidemiologist at Swinburne University, said the\u00a0restrictions were \"not unreasonable\" and would\u00a0allow Victorian health officials to closely monitor the new strain of COVID-19.", "\"What we've learnt from the last couple of years now is that you have to act really, really quickly and early,\" said Professor Thompson, adding that the virus was \"here to stay\".\u00a0", "\"This is just another argument why you need to be vaccinated because it's some protection that's way better than none.\"", "There are currently no known cases of the Omicron variant in Victoria.\u00a0", "There are currently 283\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 44\u00a0are in intensive care and 20\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 53\u00a0people were in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 52,930\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 3,358\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "Victoria has now fully vaccinated about 90\u00a0per cent of its population aged 12 and older.", "", "
What COVID-19 travel insurance doesn't cover you for(Emilia Terzon)
"]
